1. User start_mongo to bring up the mongo server (sudo needed)
2. mongo --port 10000, to bring up mongo shell
    mongo commands:
    1) show dbs
    2) use <dbname>
    3) show collections (equalvant to sql show tables)
    4) db.<collection name>.find({criteria in JSON format}).limit(5)
    5) db.<collection name>.findOne({criteria in JSON format})
    6) db.<collection name>.insert({JSON format})
    7) db.<collection name>.update({criteria JSON format}, {new JSON object})
    8) db.<collection name>.remove({criteria JSON format})
    9) db.<collection name>.drop()

3. How to install mongodb on ubuntu:
https://docs.mongodb.com/manual/tutorial/install-mongodb-on-ubuntu/
